Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

Hello Yanis, thanks for you working on this, I have two questions:

1. seems we missed glance/tests/unit/test_filesystem_store.py file.

2. why we only do migration for test files but others?

glance/api/middleware/context.py
glance/api/policy.py
glance/api/v2/image_members.py
glance/api/v2/images.py
glance/api/versions.py
glance/cmd/replicator.py
glance/common/auth.py
glance/common/wsgi.py
glance/db/sqlalchemy/migrate_repo/versions/029_location_meta_data_pickle_to_string.py (db migration file is ok probably)
glance/db/sqlalchemy/models.py:22
glance/registry/client/v1/api.py
glance/registry/client/v1/client.py
glance/schema.py
glance/store/filesystem.py

thanks.

Patch Set 1:

>> 1. seems we missed glance/tests/unit/test_filesystem_store.py file.

test_filesystem_store uses json.dump and not json.dumps, and jsonutils does not provide wrapper for json.dump yet.
So I changed all the call I could and will submit something to get jsonutils.dump into openstack.commmon

>> 2. why we only do migration for test files but others?

I wanted to do it by logical set, first tests, then in another commit code, etc...
